 Tsolo - Eastern Cape police have condemned acts of violence, attacks and murder of women that seems to have engulfed the country and also affecting the Eastern Cape. "This follows after Nolundi Ludidi, aged 30 years, disappeared on the 31st of August 2019 while she was travelling from Tsolo," said police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjen. "A case of missing person, later changed to a case of kidnapping was reported at Tsolo SAPS, but is now being investigated by a very experienced team of detectives from King William’s Town. "They have been searching for clues and following leads including searching bushy surroundings of Bisho without success. The investigation is at a very sensitive stage." Capt Tonjeni said that police are appealling to anyone, who has information that could lead to the breakthrough in this investigation to please support the police efforts and share information with the Investigating Team by calling Captain Wanele Ndinisa- 082 441 9240 or Sergeant Luxolo – 082 387 5337. "All information will be treated in the most confidential sense." Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Lt Gen Liziwe Ntshinga, has appealed for calm and rational thinking before any decision is taken by members of the public. “Our members and detective teams are doing the best they can with the resources at their disposal. We remain hopeful and optimistic for a speedy breakthrough in our investigation,” she said expressing her gratitude for concerned and supportive members of the public. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 